Cholera - Pakistan: comment 19981025.2093
Date: 2 Oct 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Pakistan Press International Information Services Ltd,
Mon 25 Sep 2000 [edited

Cholera epidemic claims 4 lives
------------------------------------
Four persons have died owing to eruption of cholera epidemic in various
areas of Muzaffarabad including Hattian Bala, Chiroie, Chenari, Leepa,
Khalana, Chikothi and several small villages.
According to details the cholera epidemic has been raging in Haitian Bala
and its adjoining villages for the last several days and 4 people including
2 from Chiroie, one from Khillana and one from Leepa have succumbed to this
fatal disease. A good number of people are being taken to general hospital
and other hospitals daily being in precarious condition.
--
